# Keep design documents authoritative

Before planning, reviewing, or changing this repository, read and follow both
canonical design documents:

@DESIGN.md
@TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md

Keep the documents synchronized with every relevant change:

- Update `DESIGN.md` in the same change whenever gameplay, game rules, balance,
  player-facing content, controls, feedback, UX, accessibility requirements,
  or acceptance criteria are introduced, changed, or removed.
- Update `TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md` in the same change whenever an architectural or
  technical decision is introduced, changed, superseded, or removed. This
  includes module responsibilities, state and event contracts, algorithms,
  dependencies, build and deployment, persistence and networking, platform
  integrations, performance, security, accessibility implementation, and test
  strategy.
- Update both documents when a decision affects both game behavior and its
  implementation.
- Treat documentation updates as part of the definition of done. Do not defer
  them to a later task, and do not document speculative decisions that were not
  adopted.
